	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="0298.jpg"/>
			<p><!--John F. Montgomery, Proposed New <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungarian</placeName>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">Jew</term><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject"> </term><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">Bill</term>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3054643/budapest.html">Budapest</placeName>, 12.1.1939, S. 1-5:</p>
      <p>Records of the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004301">Department of State</orgName> relating to internal affairs of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungary</placeName> 1930-1944,
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/4140963/washington-d-c.html">Washington</placeName> 1983 (Mikrofilm-Edition): Dokument 864.4016/125.--></p>
			<p>“I have the honor to report that considerable controversy has followed the introduction into <orgName
					ref="#ehri_dr_parliament_hungarian">Parliament</orgName> of the new <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">Jew</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">Bill</term>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-723" type="subject">Jewish</term> and the <term ref="#ehri_dr_gentile"
					type="subject">Gentile</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press</term> came to grips over it. The former
				printed articles by prominent <term ref="#ehri_dr_gentile" type="subject">Gentile</term>
				<term ref="ehri_dr_nationalities_hungarians">Hungarians</term>, many of the aristocracy, advancing <pb n="2" facs="0299.jpg"/> the
				argument that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">Bill</term> was contrary to the
				principles of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christianity</term>, violated the
				Constitution, and was inhumane. The <term ref="#ehri_dr_gentile" type="subject">Gentile</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press</term> stressed the inability of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term> to assimilate, their practicing a doctrine
				of race defense, their inferior outlook on life, and their failure to accept the general principles of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christian</term> morals, and it was predicted that the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term> would attempt <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-253" type="subject">sabotage</term> to vitiate the effects of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">Bill</term>. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-984" type="subject">Protests</term> against the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-950" type="subject">Bill</term> were expressed in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-885" type="subject">sermons</term> delivered in the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3054643/budapest.html">Budapest</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogues</term>. [...]</p>
			<pb n="3" facs="0300.jpg"/>
			<p>Many see in the presenting of this drastic <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject"
					>bill</term> a clever move by <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000191">Imrédy</persName> to
				steal the thunder of the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-474">Hungarian National
				Socialists</orgName>, to produce per se a revulsion to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-329"
					type="subject">anti-Semitic</term> sentiment (because in wide circles it is considered un-<term
					ref="ehri_dr_nationalities_hungarians">Hungarian</term> and unfair), and to make <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungary</placeName> unattractive to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term> of neighboring countries who would <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">flee</term> to it as a haven from <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642" type="subject">persecution</term>. [...]</p>
			<pb n="4" facs="0301.jpg"/>
			<p>In the last analysis, many responsible <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_hungarians">Hungarians</term> are wondering what will become
				of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term>, especially the poorer ones, when
				they are <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">deprived </term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">of their means of livelihood</term>. They feel that
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> is making a huge problem for
				itself by accelerating this problem without sufficient preparation. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">German Minister</term> told me that he did not think
				it possible for the <term ref="ehri_dr_nationalities_hungarians">Hungarians</term> to carry on an <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">anti-Semitic</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-335" type="subject">policy</term> as they conceived it because, unlike
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Germany</term>, there were no skilled <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_gentile" type="subject">Gentiles</term> to replace the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jews</term>.”</p>
